Step 1 : Add a image field to MenuItem Model
from django.db import models

class MenuItem(models.Model):
     name = models.CharField(max_length=100)
     price models.DecimalField(max_digits=6, decimal_places=2)
     image = models.ImageField(upload_to='menu_items/', blank=True, null=True)

Step 2 : Add a placeholder image to static files
i. Save your placeholder images as placeholder_menu_item.jpg
ii. Place it in:
   home/static/images/placeholder_menu_item.jpg

Step 3 : Update the menu template
<div class="menu-item">
    <img src="{% if item.image %}{{ item.image.url }}{% else %}{% static 'images/placeholder_menu_item.jpg' %}{% endif %}"
         alt="{{ item.name }}">
    <h3>{{ item.name }}</h3>
    <p>Rs{{ item.price }}</p>
</div>

Step 4 : Styling for consistent layout
.menu-item img {
    width: 200px;
    height: 150px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 5px;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
}
